description:
&lt;p&gt;Our radiology team in our Bristol Hospital currently have an opportunity for a Radiographer. Start your journey with us whilst we’ll support you to be your best.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Radiology department is comprised of one general x-ray room (DR), one CT scanner and one MRI Scanner. We facilitate the running of ultrasound and mammography lists in addition to working with two image intensifiers in theatre and Fluoroscopy. We are a small, busy department that offers a varied workload and the opportunity to work within a dedicated and supportive team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Role&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Whether you join us from the NHS or a private setting, you will find that we offer you an unrivalled opportunity to grow the respected career that you always wanted. You will benefit from our investment in state-of-the-art equipment and our commitment to give you more time with partners. As a Radiographer you will;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Deliver a high-quality diagnostic imaging service for a very varied caseload – within the department, on the ward and in theatre.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Working with leading practitioners and experiencing new practices, equipment and facilities.&lt;br /&gt;- As a clinical lead, you will enjoy scoping to develop policies and procedures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Supervising and developing more junior staff members.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Providing a service of the highest quality, delivered with sensitivity and compassion.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Person&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To succeed as a Radiographer you will have;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- High levels of technical knowledge and the ability to work quickly and accurately, with a great eye for detail.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- A caring nature – to see each patient as an individual and carry out this role with understanding and empathy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- A BSC degree in diagnostic radiography or equivalent to meet the registration requirements of the Health and Care Professions Council (HCPC)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- A postgraduate qualification in an area of specialization.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Radiation Protection Supervisor training and/ or qualification are desirable.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Post registration experience relevant to the role.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Excellent communication and team working abilities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Benefits&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We want you to be the best you can be. We promise that we will support you with training opportunities, career development options and our unique health &amp; wellbeing focused benefits package. This includes free membership across all of our Fitness &amp; Wellbeing clubs, along with free private healthcare. Not only this but we also offer a range of lifestyle and financial wellbeing benefits.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Be your best and join us in building a healthier nation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Location - Bristol&lt;br /&gt;Weekly Hours -37.5&lt;br /&gt;Contract Type - contracted&lt;br /&gt;Salary - £ 30,401 - £40,000 experience dependant&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
